The paper discusses the use of IoT and CR-WSN technologies to improve QoE and QoS in cities, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed algorithm uses reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of auction theory and game theory, which are subfields of game theory (cs.GT). The algorithm involves multiple agents interacting with each other, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the optimization of resource allocation, which is a common topic in control systems (cs.SY).
